## Your Task

Analyze the directory structure, import graph, file summaries, and per-file hints to identify logical components and their relationships.

For each component, provide:
- `:name` ‚Äî short kebab-case identifier (e.g. \"query-engine\", \"git-import\", \"http-api\")
- `:summary` ‚Äî what this component does (1-2 sentences)
- `:purpose` ‚Äî why it exists ‚Äî its role in the system
- `:layer` ‚Äî predominant architectural layer: `:core` | `:subsystem` | `:driver` | `:api` | `:util`
- `:category` ‚Äî predominant domain role: `:backend` | `:frontend` | `:infrastructure` | `:configuration` | `:data` | `:testing` | `:documentation` | `:tooling` | `:shared`
- `:patterns` ‚Äî architectural patterns spanning the component (only if clearly applicable): `:state-machine` | `:producer-consumer` | `:pipeline` | `:middleware-chain` | `:adapter`
- `:complexity` ‚Äî aggregate: `:trivial` | `:simple` | `:moderate` | `:complex` | `:very-complex`
- `:subsystem` ‚Äî coarser grouping (e.g. \"analysis-pipeline\", \"query-engine\", \"infrastructure\")
- `:files` ‚Äî list of file paths belonging to this component
- `:depends-on` ‚Äî list of other component names this depends on (based on import edges between member files)

## Rules

- Every file listed above MUST appear in exactly one component's `:files` list
- Components should contain 2-30 files typically ‚Äî not too granular, not too broad
- Component dependencies must be based on actual import edges, not speculation
- Directory structure is a strong signal for grouping, but not absolute
- Language-agnostic: identify components from structural signals (directories, imports, naming, summaries)
- Use the per-file hints as input signals, but override when the full picture says otherwise

